```css
button {
  background-color: #4CAF50; /* Bright green */
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 5px;
  cursor: pointer;
}
```

**Explanation:**

* **`button { ... }`**: This selector targets all `<button>` elements on the page.
* **`background-color: #4CAF50;`**: Sets the background color to bright green using its hexadecimal color code.
* **`color: white;`**: Sets the text color to white.
* **`padding: 10px 20px;`**: Adds padding around the text for better visual spacing.
* **`border: none;`**: Removes the default button border.
* **`border-radius: 5px;`**: Rounds the corners of the button slightly.
* **`cursor: pointer;`**: Changes the cursor to a pointer hand when hovering over the button, indicating it's clickable.

**How to use:**

1. Include this CSS code in your HTML file, either within a `<style>` tag or in a separate CSS file linked to your HTML.
2. Use the `<button>` tag in your HTML to create buttons that will be styled according to the CSS rules.

